The paper deals with finding optimal corridors for constructing a new road, which involves spatial optimization and decision making. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) or Robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The use of algorithms to solve the problem indicates that it could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper also discusses techniques for reducing computation costs and increasing accuracy, which suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
